%I A395263 #33 Jun 22 2026 19:14:30
%S A395263 4,4,5,6,8,8,8,9,10,10,10,11,11
%N A395263 Maximum number of sides of the convex hull of an n-cell polyomino.
%C A395263 a(n) is the maximum, over all n-cell polyominoes P, of the number of sides (equivalently, vertices) of the convex hull of P, where each cell of P is treated as a closed unit square in the plane.
%C A395263 The values a(1) through a(13) were determined by exhaustive enumeration of all fixed n-cell polyominoes (see A001168) using Redelmeier's algorithm, which generates each fixed polyomino exactly once. For each polyomino, the convex hull of its constituent unit squares was computed via Andrew's monotone chain on the set of cell-corner lattice points, and the maximum number of hull vertices was tracked. Since every free polyomino has at least one fixed representative, the maximum over fixed polyominoes equals the maximum over free polyominoes. The enumeration was unpruned, so all fixed n-cell polyominoes for n <= 13 were examined.
%D A395263 A. M. Andrew, Another efficient algorithm for convex hulls in two dimensions, Inform. Process. Lett., 9 (1979), 216-219.
%D A395263 D. Hugh Redelmeier, Counting polyominoes: yet another attack, Discrete Math., 36 (1981), 191-203.
%H A395263 Conner Silverstein, <a href="/A395263/a395263.txt">Python program to compute a(1)..a(13)</a>
%e A395263 For n = 3, the L-tromino with cells {(0,0), (1,0), (0,1)} has a convex hull that is a pentagon with vertices (0,0), (2,0), (2,1), (1,2), (0,2), giving a(3) = 5.
%e A395263 For n = 5, the X-pentomino (plus sign) with cells {(0,0), (1,0), (2,0), (1,1), (1,-1)} has a convex hull with 8 vertices, giving a(5) = 8. No 6-cell or 7-cell polyomino exceeds 8, so a(6) = a(7) = 8.
%e A395263 For n = 13, the polyomino with cells {(0,0), (1,0), (0,1), (2,0), (1,-1), (3,0), (3,1), (4,1), (3,2), (3,3), (2,3), (1,3), (2,4)} achieves a hull with 11 sides.
%o A395263 (Python) # See Silverstein link.
%Y A395263 Cf. A000105 (free polyominoes), A001168 (fixed polyominoes).
%Y A395263 Cf. A122133 (polyominoes with maximum convex hull area).
%Y A395263 Cf. A181785 (Wechsler's convex-hull polyominoes).
%K A395263 nonn,more
